cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless local area networks (WLANs) and proposes a decentralized AP selection scheme to improve system performance in the presence of multi-AP interference. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the signal-interference-plus noise ratio (SINR) as a metric for selecting the best AP. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of interference on system performance, which can affect multimedia applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the proposed algorithm involves distributed decision-making at the user stations (STAs) to select the best AP. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper briefly mentions the security implications of interference in WLANs.
